
[1/1] Directory renaming is a little screwy
-------------------------------------------

  Directory is empty:

skx@birthday:/mnt/redis$ redis-cli flushdb
OK

  Make a couple of directories:

skx@birthday:/mnt/redis$ mkdir foo/bar/baz -p
skx@birthday:/mnt/redis$ tree
.
└── foo
    └── bar
        └── baz
3 directories, 0 files

  Rename foo/bar -> foo/broke and we should expect to find
 foo/broke/baz - but it isn't there.

skx@birthday:/mnt/redis$ mv foo/bar/ foo/broke
skx@birthday:/mnt/redis$ ls foo/broke/

  Yet rename things back:

skx@birthday:/mnt/redis$ mv foo/broke/ foo/bar
skx@birthday:/mnt/redis$ ls foo/bar/
baz


  Issue is that we need to rename all "skx:DIR:/path/parts" entries.

Steve
--